---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    I'm Michael, a systems architect who builds apps, games, and fiction. This site is the
    one-stop shop for all of it: the <a href="/log/">devlog</a>, the
    <a href="/projects/">projects</a>, and the <a href="/writing/">writing</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>AI-assisted, not vibe-coded</h2>
  <p>
    Everything here is built with heavy AI assistance, and I document that on purpose.
    The difference between AI-assisted and AI-generated is architecture: who decided what
    to build, who caught the failure modes, who said no to scope. The devlog shows the
    work: design decisions, dead ends, prompts that failed, constraints that shipped.
    Any finished thing can be traced back to the decisions that built it.
  </p>

  <h2>Stack</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>This site: <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, markdown, zero client JS by default.</li>
    <li>Games: Godot, DAZ → Blender pre-render pipeline, Aseprite.</li>
    <li>Apps: React Native.</li>
    <li>AI: frontier models for pairing + local open weights for the long game.</li>
  </ul>
</Base>
